<section class="block-section story">
  <span class="section-tag">📖 Story</span>
  <h2>Why this block matters</h2>
  <p class="sub">The heart of the assessment: name what you sacrificed, not just what you gained.</p>
  <p>This block is the T/T heart of the unit. You quantify your plan across at least four of the seven objectives (15-minute access, housing capacity, green-blue cover, heat comfort, flood resilience, equity and displacement, mobility) and then you name what you gave up to get what you gained. Density buys housing but costs green space. Permeable land buys flood resilience but costs buildable area. Walkability can cost affordability if it pushes prices up. A plan that claims to maximise everything is hiding its trade-offs, and on the <a href="/units/unit-6/assessment-sustainable-neighbourhood-plan/">rubric</a> that is a hard cap on Thinking and Transfer. Naming the trade-off honestly is the move.</p>
  <p class="sub" style="color: var(--muted);">Full block content lands in the Unit 6 deep build.</p>
</section>

